The 3-OH is always b -oriented withorientation being ascertained by NOE interactions of H-3 with H-5. Since H-5 is axial, this interaction determines the axial orientation for H-3 and consequently a b -oriented 3-OH. In the case of agavegenin D ( 28 ), an a - orientation of H-3 and subsequently, b -orientation of 3-OH was ascertained by ROESY correlations of H-3 ( d 3.86) with H-1 a ( d 0.94), H-2 a ( d 2.04), H-4 a ( d 1.80) and H-5 ( d 1.07) (
